  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "It is always noticeable at the table of the Veneerings, that no man troubles himself much about the Veneerings themselves, and that any one who has anything to tell, generally tells it to anybody else in preference."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘The man,’ Mortimer goes on, addressing Eugene, ‘whose name is Harmon, was only son of a tremendous old rascal who made his money by Dust.’"
