    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘How did you get your wooden leg?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "Mr Wegg replied, (tartly to this personal inquiry), ‘In an accident.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Do you like it?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Well! I haven’t got to keep it warm,’ Mr Wegg made answer, in a sort of desperation occasioned by the singularity of the question."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘He hasn’t,’ repeated the other to his knotted stick, as he gave it a hug; ‘he hasn’t got—ha!—ha!—to keep it warm! Did you ever hear of the name of Boffin?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘No,’ said Mr Wegg, who was growing restive under this examination. ‘I never did hear of the name of Boffin.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Do you like it?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Why, no,’ retorted Mr Wegg, again approaching desperation; ‘I can’t say I do.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Why don’t you like it?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I don’t know why I don’t,’ retorted Mr Wegg, approaching frenzy, ‘but I don’t at all.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Now, I’ll tell you something that’ll make you sorry for that,’ said the stranger, smiling. ‘My name’s Boffin.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I can’t help it!’ returned Mr Wegg. Implying in his manner the offensive addition, ‘and if I could, I wouldn’t.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘But there’s another chance for you,’ said Mr Boffin, smiling still, ‘Do you like the name of Nicodemus? Think it over. Nick, or Noddy.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘It is not, sir,’ Mr Wegg rejoined, as he sat down on his stool, with an air of gentle resignation, combined with melancholy candour; ‘it is not a name as I could wish any one that I had a respect for, to call <em>me</em> by; but there may be persons that would not view it with the same objections.—I don’t know why,’ Mr Wegg added, anticipating another question."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Noddy Boffin,’ said that gentleman. ‘Noddy. That’s my name. Noddy—or Nick—Boffin. What’s your name?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Silas Wegg.—I don’t,’ said Mr Wegg, bestirring himself to take the same precaution as before, ‘I don’t know why Silas, and I don’t know why Wegg.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Now, Wegg,’ said Mr Boffin, hugging his stick closer, ‘I want to make a sort of offer to you. Do you remember when you first see me?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "The wooden Wegg looked at him with a meditative eye, and also with a softened air as descrying possibility of profit. ‘Let me think. I ain’t quite sure, and yet I generally take a powerful sight of notice, too. Was it on a Monday morning, when the butcher-boy had been to our house for orders, and bought a ballad of me, which, being unacquainted with the tune, I run it over to him?’"
