  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Now, you see, Rokesmith,’ he went on, ‘a literary man—<em>with</em> a wooden leg—is liable to jealousy. I shall therefore cast about for comfortable ways and means of not calling up Wegg’s jealousy, but of keeping you in your department, and keeping him in his.’"
