    "innerHtml": ""
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘You have thrown yourself away,’ said Eugene, shaking his head. ‘But you have followed the treasure of your heart. My justification is, that you had thrown that away first, dear girl!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘No. I had given it to you.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘The same thing, my poor Lizzie!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Hush! hush! A very different thing.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "There were tears in his eyes, and she besought him to close them. ‘No,’ said Eugene, again shaking his head; ‘let me look at you, Lizzie, while I can. You brave devoted girl! You heroine!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "Her own eyes filled under his praises. And when he mustered strength to move his wounded head a very little way, and lay it on her bosom, the tears of both fell."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Lizzie,’ said Eugene, after a silence: ‘when you see me wandering away from this refuge that I have so ill deserved, speak to me by my name, and I think I shall come back.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Yes, dear Eugene.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘There!’ he exclaimed, smiling. ‘I should have gone then, but for that!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "A little while afterwards, when he appeared to be sinking into insensibility, she said, in a calm loving voice: ‘Eugene, my dear husband!’ He immediately answered: ‘There again! You see how you can recall me!’ And afterwards, when he could not speak, he still answered by a slight movement of his head upon her bosom."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "The sun was high in the sky, when she gently disengaged herself to give him the stimulants and nourishment he required. The utter helplessness of the wreck of him that lay cast ashore there, now alarmed her, but he himself appeared a little more hopeful."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Ah, my beloved Lizzie!’ he said, faintly. ‘How shall I ever pay all I owe you, if I recover!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Don’t be ashamed of me,’ she replied, ‘and you will have more than paid all.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘It would require a life, Lizzie, to pay all; more than a life.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Live for that, then; live for me, Eugene; live to see how hard I will try to improve myself, and never to discredit you.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘My darling girl,’ he replied, rallying more of his old manner than he had ever yet got together. ‘On the contrary, I have been thinking whether it is not the best thing I can do, to die.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘The best thing you can do, to leave me with a broken heart?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I don’t mean that, my dear girl. I was not thinking of that. What I was thinking of was this. Out of your compassion for me, in this maimed and broken state, you make so much of me—you think so well of me—you love me so dearly.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Heaven knows I love you dearly!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘And Heaven knows I prize it! Well. If I live, you’ll find me out.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I shall find out that my husband has a mine of purpose and energy, and will turn it to the best account?’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I hope so, dearest Lizzie,’ said Eugene, wistfully, and yet somewhat whimsically. ‘I hope so. But I can’t summon the vanity to think so. How can I think so, looking back on such a trifling wasted youth as mine! I humbly hope it; but I daren’t believe it. There is a sharp misgiving in my conscience that if I were to live, I should disappoint your good opinion and my own—and that I ought to die, my dear!’"
  },
