  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘Is it though!’ said Riderhood. ‘Who’d have thought it, from the looks on it! <em>would</em> you be so kind as write your name upon it, learned governor?’ (In a wheedling tone.)"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "Bradley hesitated for a moment; but placed his usual signature, enlarged, upon the board."
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘I ain’t a learned character myself,’ said Riderhood, surveying the class, ‘but I do admire learning in others. I should dearly like to hear these here young folks read that there name off, from the writing.’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "The arms of the class went up. At the miserable master’s nod, the shrill chorus arose: ‘Bradley Headstone!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "‘No?’ cried Riderhood. ‘You don’t mean it? Headstone! Why, that’s in a churchyard. Hooroar for another turn!’"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
